text: Given how difficult it is to make long term profits from automation, do you guys do this for: "fun", or "for the aim of eventually finding that elusive profitable strategy", or "it's not difficult, I make a living from this, have done for years!" ?

elements.text: Given how difficult it is to make long term profits from automation, do you guys do this for: "fun", or "for the aim of eventually finding that elusive profitable strategy", or "it's not difficult, I make a living from this, have done for years!" ?

text: Id be interested to see what the big guys respond to this <@U01PJ5YMFBJ> as everyone journey is different. For me at least it was an idea, that started as a hobby and I guess the end goal of making money if I was lucky but obviously at the time I was clueless about the landscape (and still am at times it feels).  After some small trail and error I found an edge but it took little a longer for a real break through which ultimately lead to this being a full time gig. I think like most things in life when you struggling to achieve a goal it looks very hard / impossible until you do it, then your mind switches and thinks that isn't so hard and sets a newer even harder goal to achieve.  I guess a last point is, that its quite easy to get drawn into a mind set where your comparing yourself against others, which sometimes can be good for motivation and to show you what is possible but setting a series of smaller more manageable goals that you can consistently hit is going to push you forward best
